Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.55,0:00:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The most precious moment in life is the time of decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.37,0:00:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace, but it also leaves us with many lessons to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.27,0:00:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ketsudan (decision)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.27,0:00:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Use your wisdom Use your head Keep thinking it you're a man
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.13,0:00:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you cry or laugh, it depends on your decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.20,0:01:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be arrogant even if you win Don't cry even if you lose
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.06,0:01:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Man does not show tears
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.58,0:01:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Tatsunoko Production
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.11,0:01:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Prior to the start of the Pacific War, in October 1941, a meeting to discuss the Southern Operations was held at the Army War College for several days.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.01,0:01:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Among the Southern Operations, the leading role of the Philippine operation was the 14th Army under the command of Lieutenant General Masaharu Homma,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.56,0:02:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to which the 5th Flight Group was assigned. However, there was an important problem with the operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.25,0:02:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It was unclear if the US military would fight in the capital, Manila, or stay in the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.73,0:02:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,> The mission of the 14th Army is to destroy the major enemy bases in the Philippines. That means the city of Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.73,0:02:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I want the 14th Army's main force to land 10 day after the start of the war and occupy the city of Manila 35 days later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.25,0:02:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, the plan is that the 48th Division and the 5th Flight Group will be diverted to Operation Java-Malayan after a pause.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.28,0:02:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that time will be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.39,0:02:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,> Is the purpose of the Philippine operation to capture the city of Manila or to destroy enemy troops? I want to clarify it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.80,0:03:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,> I think that the enemy ts likely to escape to the Bataan Peninsula, as it did during the American-Spanish War.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.21,0:03:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. If the enemy can escape to the Bataan Peninsula, it will be difficult to destroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.25,0:03:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, if the 48th Division and the 5th Flight Group were later pulled out by Operation Java-Malayan, our troops would be thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.18,0:03:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,> The Bataan Peninsula is a natural fortress. It would be difficult if they escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.90,0:03:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we should also consider fighting in Bataan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.83,0:03:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,> No, I don't think it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.87,0:03:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,> The enemy is mainly the militia, and MacArthur must be thinking of a defensive operation in Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.21,0:03:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,After the Philippine Operation, the Java Operation is planned. Therefore, in order to send the 48th Division to Java,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.97,0:03:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,> If the enemy escapes to the Bataan Peninsula, I think it should be dealt with slowly later.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.14,0:03:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,> I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.45,0:03:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,> On November 3rd, the Chief of Staff, General Sugiyama, submitted a draft of this operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.70,0:04:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,> First, the purpose of the operation: to destroy the enemy in the Philippines and destroy its main base.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.39,0:04:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Second operational purpose: The Army, in cooperation with the Navy, will land on Luzon and quickly capture Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.87,0:04:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it necessary to write down what happens when the enemy escapes to the Bataan Peninsula?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.59,0:04:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,> The authority to make that decision is left to the commander of the 14th Army. I think you don't have to write it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.07,0:04:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Battle of Bataan and Corregidor
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.42,0:04:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,On December 8th, the 11th Air Fleet's formation of Mitsubishi G4M Zero fighters, informed by the successful surprise attack on Pearl Harbor,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.83,0:04:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,ambushed the US Air Force bases in the Philippines: Clark Air Base and Iva.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.49,0:04:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It destroyed about 100 US planes waiting on the ground and the US Air force in the Philippines was destroyed in a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.49,0:05:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Subsequently, the main force under the command of the 14th Army Commander, Lieutenant General Masaharu Homma, formed a convoy of 76 ships
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.73,0:05:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and was escorted by the Third Fleet under the command of Vice Admiral Takahashi, and went south into the southern waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.56,0:05:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,> As for the plan on the day of the landing, a successful landing is the first priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.39,0:05:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,> Its okay. The soldiers are enthusiastic and are competing for the first ride in Manila. Morale is quite strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.90,0:05:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, MacArthur must be fully prepared and waiting for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.73,0:05:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,> The problem is Bataan, but we can think about it at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.11,0:05:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,> No, sir, we have to take Manila all at once and not give the enemy time to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.35,0:06:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,> The 14th Army's main force split into two and landed in the Lingayen Gulf on December 22nd, and in Lamon Bay on December 24th.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.80,0:06:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,From the south and north, they launched their march towards the City of Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.52,0:06:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,> The Japanese army!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.18,0:06:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn back!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.66,0:07:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,> The US army could not fight against the tremendous advance of the Japanese army.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.11,0:07:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,> The enemy forces in the Central region are estimated to be 5 divisions, and 3 of them have already been devastated.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.28,0:07:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,> What is the situation of the enemy army in Manila?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.39,0:07:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>I don't know the exact situation, but some of them have been hit hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.39,0:07:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,> So I wonder if the enemy is staying in Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.18,0:07:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,> Although just a part of their force, enemies near Iba are retreating to the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.42,0:07:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,> Finally, are they going to stay on the Bataan Peninsula?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.70,0:07:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,> The advance of the Japanese army was narrowed down to Manila from the north and south, and the fall of Manila seemed to be just a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.11,0:08:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,General Douglas MacArthur, commander of the United States Army Forces of the Far East, is now faced with an important strategic decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.87,0:08:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,> Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.32,0:08:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,> The advance of the Japanese army is faster than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.83,0:08:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is supported by a powerful air force and equipped with a large number of tanks and field artillery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.63,0:09:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,> All right. Make Manila an open city and withdraw all troops to the Bataan Peninsula and Corregidor Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.28,0:09:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,> It's War Plan Orange.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.01,0:09:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,> Yeah. Move the military headquarters to Corregidor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.28,0:09:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,> Defend here until the rescue army comes from our home country.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.59,0:09:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,> We can absolutely protect the Bataan Peninsula and Corregidor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.18,0:09:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if San Fernando, the entrance to the Bataan Peninsula, is captured, our withdrawal is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.49,0:09:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,> No quarter given. Stop the Japanese here until the withdrawal is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.42,0:09:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,> I will do it in honor of the US military.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.39,0:09:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Manila is declared an open city and General MacArthur plans to blow up the bridge at 6 AM on January 1st.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.25,0:09:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,His entire army is ordered to withdrawal by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.63,0:09:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All US military facilities in Manila were burned down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.25,0:10:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,"Open City". In other words, a cloth was put on it to indicate that the city was defenseless,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.08,0:10:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and a truck full of soldiers, weapons, and ammunition passed by it in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.32,0:10:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,> Sir, the enemy has escaped to the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.83,0:10:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The 48th Division Commander strongly advises us not to let the enemy escape to the Bataan Peninsula, and to put Manila behind us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.49,0:10:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,> Report from the reconnaissance aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.73,0:10:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Large units of enemies are retreating to the Bataan Peninsula one after another. In addition, it seems that they are moving from the direction of Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.32,0:10:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,> It's bad. There is no point in robbing Manila, which has become vacant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.97,0:10:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,> No, the enemy is also desperately fighting back. It will not easy to withdraw to the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.49,0:10:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,> No, it is a clear withdrawal. We should destroy the bridge, prevent their retreat, and hit the Luzon Plain all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.94,0:11:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,> No, it may be a trap. > Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.77,0:11:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,> The intention of the Imperial Headquarters is to defeat the enemy and quickly capture Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.59,0:11:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,48th Division must defeat their enemies and move towards Manila at once
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.04,0:11:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,> For some time, it was what was expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.63,0:11:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,> Lieutenant General Homma thought to disobey for a moment, but kept the duty of all military personnel to obey the orders of his superiors
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.45,0:11:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and aimed at Manila as instructed by the Imperial Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.08,0:11:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,> This allowed the US military to safely withdrew to the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.04,0:12:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,On January 2nd, Manila fell and Japanese troops entered, but this did not end the Philippine operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.14,0:12:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because most of the US troops stood on the Bataan Peninsula and Corregidor Fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.01,0:12:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to completely occupy and secure Manila City, it is necessary to secure Manila Bay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.87,0:12:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to secure Manila Bay, the US troops on the Bataan Peninsula and Corregidor Island must be conquered.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.70,0:12:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, Bataan must fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.01,0:13:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.21,0:13:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,> The Bataan Peninsula is 48km long and 24km wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.66,0:13:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The west and south were protected by cliffs, inaccessible from the sea, and the entire peninsula Was covered in jungle. It was a natural fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.56,0:13:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, the number of US troops was more than 80,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.08,0:14:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,> It's okay. We wont be defeated for three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.01,0:14:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,> Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.56,0:14:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,> The 48th Division was transferred to Operation Java as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.90,0:15:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,3000 soldiers of the 65th Brigade under the command of Lieutenant General Nara landed on the Lingayen Gulf on January 1st.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.18,0:15:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They had no time to rest and relied On an inaccurate 1 / 200,000 scale map to pursue enemies on the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.83,0:15:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese did not see General MacArthur's withdrawal from Bataan as a strategic retreat, but as a mere rout.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.83,0:15:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,> The Japanese troops underestimated the US troops who retreated to the Bataan Peninsula, and were hit harder than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.90,0:15:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,On February 8th, Commander of the 14th Army, Lieutenant General Homma, gathered his staff members
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.73,0:15:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and held a planning meeting On measures to carry out the operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.25,0:15:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,> We are now in a critical phase.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.11,0:15:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The question is whether to continue the attack or suspend it and rebuild our formations. I would like to hear your opinions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.45,0:16:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,> The attack should continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.73,0:16:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,> That is impossible. With the current combat power, it will only be wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.39,0:16:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,> We can do it. Until now, the operations have been left to each unit, but from now on, command will be unified at military headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.21,0:16:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It we focus your attacks on the east and west coasts, you will always succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.11,0:16:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,> Yeah. Attack is the best defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.73,0:16:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If we continue to attack even with a part of our forces and replenish our troops in the meantime, we can go on the offensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.25,0:16:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, the soldiers are exhausted and their damage is great. It is better to take measures to wait for our troops to recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.59,0:16:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Opinions were divided into two camps, and there was a fierce controversy, forcing the commander to make a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.42,0:16:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,On February 10th, the commander made a decision and telegraphed the General Staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.01,0:16:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,> The attack was stopped. The soldiers are over the limit of their physical strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.63,0:16:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stand fighting like this anymore. I dare to be ashamed as a military commander and ask for reinforcements in this section.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.49,0:17:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, at the General Staff Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.49,0:17:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,> What is the 14th Army doing? It's an army of shame. The attack should continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.25,0:17:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is that the Southern operation is going well, only the Philippines are not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.66,0:17:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,> The Southern Expeditionary Army commander also wants an attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.04,0:17:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,> Isn't it necessary to write about the case when the enemy escapes to the Bataan Peninsula?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.87,0:17:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The authority to make that decision is left to the commander of the 14th Army, I think you don't have to write it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.42,0:17:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,> It was the General Staff Headquarters who advocated the primary objective of capturing Manila, and the Southern Expeditionary Army Command, who was in command.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.80,0:17:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But now the commander's decision hasn't changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.35,0:17:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A week later, Lieutenant General Homma telegraphed the commander of the Southern Expeditionary Army,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.66,0:17:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The message was still to stop the attack and ask for reinforcements.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.56,0:18:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day, the Southern Expeditionary Army command dismissed several staff members, including the Chief of Staff of the 14th Army.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.94,0:18:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Several members of the General Staff Operations Division were newly incorporated into the 14th Army,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.77,0:18:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and an operation for a second total attack on the Bataan Peninsula was planned for.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.21,0:18:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,A truck road was also built in the jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.90,0:18:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,30,000 reinforcements, mainly from the 4th Division, have also arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.87,0:18:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,> The night before the second all out attack was a quiet one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.28,0:19:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well-trained soldiers slept confidently and comfortably.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.25,0:19:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,> The following day, April 3rd, the second all out attack on the Bataan Peninsula began.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.70,0:20:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,> Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.87,0:20:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,>On April 9th, the US military on the Bataan Peninsula was finally defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.70,0:21:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The number of POWs was 70,000. Many were thin because of hunger and malaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.90,0:21:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,> All that remains is just to attack the enemy on Corregidor Island, but that requires transporting 70,000 POWs rearwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.01,0:21:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the POWs Are sick with malaria, or malnourished.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.83,0:21:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why, if we leave them alone as they are, they will be wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.04,0:21:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If we transport them to the rear, there are field hospitals.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.18,0:21:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to set up a first aid station every few kilometers and deliver them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.94,0:21:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, the number of POWs is 70,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.52,0:21:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,> Collect as many trucks as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.18,0:21:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.97,0:21:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,> I leave it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.77,0:21:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,> However, despite the commander's order, there were few Japanese trucks and it was difficult to procure them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.14,0:21:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the POWs had to walk 88km on the hot road.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.83,0:22:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 2,300 POWs died in the Bataan Death March, but this was far less than if they were left on the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.11,0:22:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the US still called this a "death march."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.21,0:22:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Already, General MacArthur had transferred command to Major General Wainwright and had escaped from Corregidor Island to Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.56,0:22:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The words "I shall return", which included a counterattack against the Philippines, made the Allied side excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.63,0:22:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Next to the Bataan Peninsula is Corregidor Island, but the US military was no longer willing to resist, and on May 6th
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.49,0:22:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Corregidor Island also fell, and the Philippine campaign was completed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.73,0:23:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,However, shortly afterwards, the commander of the 14th Army was transferred to a reserve role.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.42,0:23:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The commander obeyed the orders of the Imperial Headquarters and captured Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.25,0:23:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking of the hardships of his subordinates, he abandoned his pride as a military commander and sought reinforcements.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.32,0:23:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He moved the Bataan prisoners to Corregidor to avoid useless deaths and injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.73,0:23:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the commander's weak decisions made on the harsh battlefield were seen as a fatal flaw in a commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.20,0:24:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace, but it also leaves us with many lessons to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.92,0:24:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a man, test your strength It you are a man, burn your hope
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.44,0:24:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you area man, don't let yourself down
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.20,0:25:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I and you are men and men bleed the same bright red blood.
